initialize(address).details: Initializes the contract with the given parameters.

params._factoryStorage: The address of the Uniswap V2 factory.

issuanceIndexTokens(address,uint256,uint.details: Issues index tokens by swapping the input token.

params._tokenIn: The address of the input token.
params._tokenInSwapFee: The swap version of the input token.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

redemption(uint256,address,uint24).details: Redeems index tokens for the specified output token.

params._tokenOut: The address of the output token.
params._tokenOutSwapFee: The swap version of the output token.
params.amountIn: The amount of index tokens to redeem.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.
